    "summary": "Elsa Scholte is a passionate communication expert with 20 years of experience in all fields of communication for international (development) organisations. With degrees in both cultural anthropology and communication, she is able to work in diverse cultural contexts and has extensive knowledge and experience in public relations, campaign management, fundraising, social media and website management and publications. \n\nDuring her years in Suriname she moved to the field of communication for development, with a special focus on health communication and communication for disaster preparedness and relief.\n\nElsa specializes in creative and strategic communication solutions for development organisations, which offers an optimal environment for her diverse skill set. She knows how to involve stakeholders, and giving them the confidence and motivation to contribute to development, be it their own or that of the millions in the world still living in poverty.\n\nWith a strong belief in the power of visual communication, Elsa is also an experienced visual meeting and strategy facilitator. She is able to convert complex strategies into appealing stories for a larger audience. ",
